# Docs Sync Rules — JonBeatz

## Path standards

- **START-HERE.md** is the primary entry point
- Profile root: `D:\Hermes\projects\JonBeatz` — never MSC deploy paths unless Jon opens MSC repo
- Use relative links or `${workspace}` — avoid hardcoding sibling repo paths in daily docs

## Version tracking

- Sync version across `package.json`, `TRUTH.md`, `MASTER-COMMANDS.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`
- Use **`npm run version:sync`** (Python UTF-8) — never rewrite README badges from raw PowerShell
- Run **`npm run encoding:check`** before doc commits; **`npm run docs:sync`** runs it automatically
- **`.gitattributes`** enforces UTF-8 + LF on markdown and scripts
- **ReCall.md** captures significant session outcomes
- **Restore-Points.md** updated at meaningful milestones (backup, release, incident recovery)

## Issue management

- Every bug fix → append **`.cursor/docs/ISSUES-RESOLVED.md`** or run `npm run log:fix`
- Include root cause and shortest verified recovery path
- Reference related files changed

## Rules management

- No contradictory rules across `.mdc` files
- When removing a feature, document in ISSUES-RESOLVED with reason
- Flag duplicate or conflicting rules during `npm run docs:sync`

## Commit discipline

- Doc-only changes: `docs:` prefix when Jon requests commit
- Update docs when behavior changes (scripts, rituals, MCP setup)
- Do **not** auto-commit unless Jon asks

## MCP + skills

- Project MCP secrets live in `.env.local` — sync with `npm run sync:mcp-env`
- Never commit real API keys in `.cursor/mcp.json`
- UI skills read order: NovaMira-Design → MSC-UI-Taste → Premium-UI
